The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, March 31 (PTI): The Supreme Court has taken serious note of a petition that alleged the Chhattisgarh government was arming people in the Salwa Judum movement to fight Naxalites. You (the state government) cannot give arms to somebody and allow him to kill, the court said. You will be an abettor of the offence under Section 302.                   
	Srinagar (PTI): At least 11 Jammu and Kashmir Mass Movement activists were detained on Monday for demonstrating in spite of prohibitory orders. The separatist group, affiliated to the Hurriyat Conference, was demanding to know the whereabouts of those allegedly missing from the custody of state security forces.                   
	Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): Malayalam poet Kadammanitta Ramakrishnan died of cancer at a private hospital in his hometown, Pathanamthitta, on Monday. He was 73. Ramakrishnan was elected to the Kerala Assembly in 1996 and headed the Marxist cultural forum, Purogamana Kalasahitya Sangham, for a long time.                   
	Ahmedabad (PTI): A man caught stealing a bicycle was beaten to death by a group of villagers in Narmada district on Monday. Bharat Tadvi was taken to hospital where he died. Police have registered a murder case against the villagers.                  
	Chennai (PTI): The Tamil Nadu government on Monday announced that yoga would be made a compulsory subject in all schools in the state from the next academic year. School education minister Thangam Thennarasu said the government has trained 1.1 lakh teachers for this purpose.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): Two children have been killed in a landslide in Leh district. Their bodies were found on Sunday and a hunt is on for the body of a third child. They were playing when the landslide struck.                                                                                                                           
